{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/settingsbackend\/pathchanged(path:origintag:)"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SettingsBackend","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SettingsBackend\/SettingsBackendProtocol-Implementations"]]},"metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"pathChanged","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"path"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UnsafePointer"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"gchar","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":">!, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"originTag","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gpointer","text":"gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"?)"}],"modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"title":"pathChanged(path:originTag:)","role":"symbol","symbolKind":"method","roleHeading":"Instance Method","externalID":"s:3GIO23SettingsBackendProtocolPAAE11pathChanged0E09originTagySPys4Int8VGSg_SvSgtF::SYNTHESIZED::s:3GIO15SettingsBackendC","extendedModule":"GIO"},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"abstract":[{"text":"Signals that all keys below a given path may have possibly changed.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Backend implementations should call this if an entire path of keys"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"have possibly changed their values.","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SettingsBackend\/pathChanged(path:originTag:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"pathChanged"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"path"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UnsafePointer"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gchar"},{"text":">!, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"originTag","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gpointer"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil)"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"text":"Discussion","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"path"},{"type":"text","text":" must be a valid path (ie starting and ending with a slash and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"not containing ‘\/\/’)."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The meaning of this signal is that any of the key which has a name"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"starting with "},{"code":"path","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" may have changed.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The same rules for when notifications must occur apply as per"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_settings_backend_changed()"},{"type":"text","text":".  This call might be an appropriate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reasponse to a ‘reset’ call but implementations are also free to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"explicitly list the keys that were affected by that call if they can"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"easily do so.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For efficiency reasons, the implementation should strive for "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"path"},{"text":" to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"be as long as possible (ie: the longest common prefix of all of the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"keys that were changed) but this is not strictly required.  As an"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"example, if this function is called with the path of “\/” then every","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"single key in the application will be notified of a possible change."}]}]}],"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/SettingsBackend":{"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSettingsBackend"},{"text":" interface defines a generic interface for","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"non-strictly-typed data that is stored in a hierarchy. To implement"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"an alternative storage backend for [class","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Settings","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"], you need to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"implement the "},{"code":"GSettingsBackend","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" interface and then make it implement the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"extension point "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_SETTINGS_BACKEND_EXTENSION_POINT_NAME"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SettingsBackend","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SettingsBackend","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"SettingsBackend","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/settingsbackend","title":"SettingsBackend"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO":{"type":"topic","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","title":"GIO","url":"\/documentation\/gio","role":"collection","kind":"symbol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/Settings":{"title":"Settings","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/settings","abstract":[{"type":"text","text"